author: brane
msg: Don't disable asserts in Win32 Release builds, because that can hide
bugs. Newer versions of the release MSVCRT contain runtime support for
assert, so this should no longer be a problem (note however that we
might have to ship MSVCRT.dll with the Windows binaries now).
* build/generator/msvc_dsp.ezt: Don't pass NDEBUG to rc.exe.
